<p>swim in the moonlight last evening and there must have been at least 4000 ducking about. Very little swimming is now done in the day as there had been too many casualties.</p>
<p>Friday 25th June [1915]<br/>Corp Coleman &amp; Lieut Hodgens returned to-day. A Cruiser came over to-day &amp; fired a few broadsides into part of hill no 2. She was surrounded by Torpedo Destroyers to protect her from Submarines.</p>
<p>Corp A Hurly Pvte A Ball, H Tyrrell on beach 9th Battalion</p>
